data.description: PRICE REDUCTION! Amidst the serene beauty of Johns Island, this 3-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom gem is your ticket to Lowcountry living at its finest. With 1,698 square feet of space, this delightful residence in the Summertrees neighborhood offers a warm and inviting atmosphere that beckons you to call it home.Upon entering, you'll be greeted by an open and airy floor plan that seamlessly connects the living, dining, and kitchen areas. The heart of the home, the kitchen, is a culinary enthusiast's dream with modern appliances, ample counter space, and a convenient center island. Natural light filters in through large windows, enhancing the inviting atmosphere throughout the home.The 3 spacious bedrooms offer versatility and comfort, perfect for accommodating a growing family or creating the ideal work-from-home space. The primary bedroom features an ensuite bathroom, creating a private retreat within your home. The additional 2.5 bathrooms are beautifully appointed for convenience.  Living on Johns Island offers a unique blend of tranquility and convenience. You'll be captivated by the island's picturesque landscapes, from expansive farms to moss-draped oak trees. This community boasts a rich history and a tight-knit, welcoming atmosphere. Enjoy peaceful walks along country roads or explore the scenic trails at Angel Oak Park, a local treasure.  Proximity to Charleston, Folly Beach, and Kiawah Island: The location of 2830 August Road is the epitome of convenience. Downtown Charleston, with its historic charm, culinary delights, and cultural attractions, is just a short drive away. Meanwhile, the vibrant shores of Folly Beach and the world-renowned Kiawah Island golf courses are within easy reach for weekend getaways and recreation.  This home provides the ideal opportunity to embrace the Lowcountry lifestyle, where Southern charm meets modern comfort. Don't miss your chance to make this piece of paradise your own. Schedule a showing today and experience the allure of Johns Island living.
